mponent\" style=\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\" width=\"100%\">\\n      <tr>\\n       <td class=\"body-component__content\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; mso-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt; padding: 0px 10px;\">\\n        <table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"header\" width=\"100%\">\\n         <tr>\\n          <td class=\"body-header-container\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; mso-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;\">\\n           <h2 style=\"font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 26px; line-height: 28px; font-weight: normal; border-top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; padding-top: 12px; margin: 20px 0px 0px;\">\\n            Podcast\\n           </h2>\\n          </td>\\n         </tr>\\n        </table>\\n        <p style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif; margin: 16px 0;\">\\n         This week\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Money Stuff podcast episode is out now, in which Katie and I discuss the MMTLP squeeze(s), the MAAX zips squeeze, 2 a.m. private equity interviews and replicating options using a mix of cash and stock. You can listen to the episode\\n         <a href=\"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35896109.283281/aHR0cHM6Ly9saW5rLnBvZHRyYWMuY29tL2Y4eTd2ODlv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb1c12d8b\" itemprop=\"StoryLink\" itemscope=\"itemscope\" target=\"_blank\">\\n          here\\n         </a>\\n         :\\n        </p>\\n        <div class=\"body-image\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px;\">\\n         <a href=\"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35896109.283281/aHR0cHM6Ly9saW5rLnBvZHRyYWMuY29tL2Y4eTd2ODlv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCb1c12d8b\" target=\"_blank\">\\n          <!--[if mso]>\\n<table width=\"550\"><tr><td><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/i0sZ4OHezJtw/v0/-1x-1.png\" width=\"550\" /></td></tr></table>\\n<div style=\"display:none\">\\n<![endif]-->\\n          <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjW